<subSubSection id="5477F85E42321890299321E882057ACF" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" type="chemistry">
<paragraph id="5BC3E66AEDC3326FF985D71C1FA471F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Chemistry.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D9CC91E0D7239F892C72B5CBC3F2953C" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Thallus K-, C+/-. Medulla I+ violet. Gyrophoric acid, 4-O-demethylplanaic acid or no substances detected by TLC.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="219ED62501960EC8BE88FFD6A6CBFD50" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="4E554CF54AA55EBEE8DC83D6409D636E" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Ecology and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6AADCA57E9F0C23A1A96AE07D8EF8E46" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">In China, growing on rock, sandstone, granite or Qilian jade (rare), from elevations of 3100 to 4800 m in the alpine zone of west China and from 1200 to 1900 m in the steppe of north China. This genus is known from China, Europe, Iran, Mongolia, Romania, Russia, and USA.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="84BCBDA987BF3C3BBAF67BC41A39A357" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" type="notes">
<paragraph id="E14BCB6777F71AED6CCC13A112E7A419" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BE7F1A5BDD92B27A4C311F9D65AC4B60" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">
The five-loci phylogenetic analysis showed that the species with lecanorine apothecia formed a novel lineage and should be excluded from 
<taxonomicName id="B93821BA287C14CD0561E9488429F4F4" authorityName="Rambold &amp; Pietschm., Bibliotheca Lichenologica 34: 239" authorityYear="1989" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Immersaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Immersaria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="99C79E5738C919D327938A11CD8AD4C5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Immersaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; thus, they are here treated as a new genus 
<taxonomicName id="3AEB0479AE54DC901234027BC7365693" authorityName="C. M. Xie, Lu L. Zhang &amp; Li S. Wang" authorityYear="2022" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Lecaimmeria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecaimmeria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D865BCFCD5650D2661887B94552D419E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Lecaimmeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="99E10333AE5DC4A46811702162DA53DA" authorityName="C. M. Xie, Lu L. Zhang &amp; Li S. Wang" authorityYear="2022" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Lecaimmeria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecaimmeria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="81C3247D00386D9AF4989B7EE47A8396" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Lecaimmeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from related genera by its glossy surface, orange or red-brown areolae with margins, the amyloid medulla, the red-brown immersed lecanorine apothecia, the orange epihymenium with a plectenchyma and the 
<taxonomicName id="896BFBA915E1AC3CA2334C99D4993833" authorityName="Koerber" authorityYear="1855" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Porpidiaceae" genus="Porpidia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Porpidia" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3BF237C6A69B9B32CB91E21FC14C8B63" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Porpidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-type asci with eight halonate and non-amyloid ascospores. In China, the genus is distributed in alpine areas, high altitude desert-steppe areas or high latitude steppe. Almost all the species of 
<taxonomicName id="9D573B9E98FAEB3C6451C2AD5D0E73B3" authorityName="C. M. Xie, Lu L. Zhang &amp; Li S. Wang" authorityYear="2022" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Lecaimmeria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecaimmeria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="88EFAF2836615FE46196BB785C5B029B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Lecaimmeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grow on granite or sandstone, with the exception of one species, 
<taxonomicName id="13514A7F263D5F4AF310C359D5D98CF9" genus="L." lsidName="L. tuberculosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="tuberculosa">
<emphasis id="2BBE7A8F286AB5A40703C40E7DA7801A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">L. tuberculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which grows on jade. Interestingly, the margin of conidiomata and areolae of 
<taxonomicName id="2A239B21FF8149272D42B10814B7FBE2" authorityName="C. M. Xie &amp; Xin Y. Wang" authorityYear="2022" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Lecaimmeria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecaimmeria tuberculosa" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="tuberculosa">
<emphasis id="426223517A781B45108D8BA3D36955B2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Lecaimmeria tuberculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear with heavily jade-green pruinose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B6099FF5BD1FAF2440B07A915A5F16E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">
The immersed apothecia and brown thallus of 
<taxonomicName id="CFB00AABC0A21177245F0EBFA79598C3" authorityName="C. M. Xie, Lu L. Zhang &amp; Li S. Wang" authorityYear="2022" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Lecaimmeria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecaimmeria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7739B685E38CBE0EA018E50D3A045932" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Lecaimmeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
often resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="A22DEA4A585466E2877CAF8D72FC75D8" authorityName="Rambold &amp; Pietschm., Bibliotheca Lichenologica 34: 239" authorityYear="1989" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Immersaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Immersaria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49C85CFC2DA6B31CC2C85BA08CBC7AEB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Immersaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="05CBFC0BB3B2311DECD986AA59BF411D" authorityName="C. M. Xie, Lu L. Zhang &amp; Li S. Wang" authorityYear="2022" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Lecaimmeria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecaimmeria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B6A3013B9C925566FE1C8542FB6258F3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Lecaimmeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in its red-brown lecanorine apothecia, often with a white margin, their orange epihymenium with a plectenchyma and the thallus containing gyrophoric acid. This genus might be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="1F687A28AD25E1730AC0BD0C13E2D8A3" authorityName="Hafellner &amp; Cl.Roux" authorityYear="1984" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Bellemerea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bellemerea" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F31F5653CA90A8553E971DF3A2C031E4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Bellemerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its lecanorine apothecia and the 
<taxonomicName id="90059CE9A88D87CE89F6FF448DE3C643" authorityName="Koerber" authorityYear="1855" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Porpidiaceae" genus="Porpidia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Porpidia" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="592EA8EE20EFB477CA88650884793D1B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Porpidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-type asci with halonate ascospores, but the latter genus differs in its amyloid ascospores.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4162D1D74164E5181598946FF536D115" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">
Three species, previously included in 
<taxonomicName id="5B32484EEDCFA4D119C453D7576234A0" authorityName="Rambold &amp; Pietschm., Bibliotheca Lichenologica 34: 239" authorityYear="1989" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Immersaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Immersaria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BB1A4366D4356AABA5E9D98447F7FBBE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Immersaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1205A701CB1FF56432EC8E52A555C6B6" genus="I." lsidName="I. cupreoatra" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="cupreoatra">
<emphasis id="7738B4F7E18EB75DE829A32D23D2B67B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">I. cupreoatra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CE5F4A77BB36364D6E4C814C6B1E4FF7" genus="I." lsidName="I. iranica" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="iranica">
<emphasis id="F6BEAFFCE1C7B172A99D6E455B2749BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">I. iranica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A08B915E9AA5907CB9AD646284D17F62" genus="I." lsidName="I. mehadiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="mehadiana">
<emphasis id="8CB564E03F79C54EB54218DC15692486" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">I. mehadiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, have lecanorine apothecia, but two of these, 
<taxonomicName id="F214527949BFE0CA75F2FE827A8556C2" genus="I." lsidName="I. cupreoatra" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="cupreoatra">
<emphasis id="69A441FFEEF90C996E74A2274B2525EF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">I. cupreoatra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DFD84B05257BAB2E2E904987698A5AC4" genus="I." lsidName="I. mehadiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="mehadiana">
<emphasis id="0FC33E20E7CD4CCCDBB5180FC19FDE40" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">I. mehadiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, currently lack molecular sequences. We suggest that these three species should be transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="3544FEFA02FBFD16D5DACD1CF60C00F2" authorityName="C. M. Xie, Lu L. Zhang &amp; Li S. Wang" authorityYear="2022" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Lecaimmeria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecaimmeria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="21F0618279E8904932BD66E232375FA6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Lecaimmeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the following factors. Their morphology is consistent with 
<taxonomicName id="939E9BE36BF55476D58A45F6CACAF3F0" authorityName="C. M. Xie, Lu L. Zhang &amp; Li S. Wang" authorityYear="2022" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Lecaimmeria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecaimmeria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1A3FE0ED3F80587E2EDA783E5DFD7E33" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Lecaimmeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to molecular results and comparisons with type specimens, high-resolution photographs of the type materials and the original descriptions. One unknown &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="009EAD250FB1D573946D5C0D1DA0E6F9" authorityName="Rambold &amp; Pietschm., Bibliotheca Lichenologica 34: 239" authorityYear="1989" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Immersaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Immersaria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66E29FC5BE590076176A25025FFD45E2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Immersaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; species from Macedonia is sister to 
<taxonomicName id="618D599C1566330B76878F2F2A98FD92" authorityName="C. M. Xie" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Valadb., Sipman &amp; Rambold" baseAuthorityYear="2022" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Lecaimmeria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecaimmeria iranica" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="iranica">
<emphasis id="979BC78F34AD5D9E9D202E4D934F752A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Lecaimmeria iranica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the phylogenetic tree (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="86CD9E7F21841199B112689EAB640663" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Phylogenetic tree constructed from Maximum Likelihood analyses in Lecaimmeria, based on the concatenated nrITS-nrLSU-RPB 1 - RPB 2 dataset. Maximum Likelihood bootstrap probabilities above 70 % (left) and Bayesian Inference posterior probabilities above 0.9 (right) are given at the nodes. Solid purple rectangle: areolae margin white; solid grey rectangle: areolae margin black; hollow purple rectangle: areolae margin jade green pigmented. Solid blue circle gyrophoric acid; hollow blue circle: none." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.87.72614.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646456" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">3</figureCitation>
), but comparison with high-resolution photograph and previous records (
<bibRefCitation id="945EC78B841E8581280B78924E94DE79" DOI="https://doi.org/10.13158/heia.30.2.2017.431" author="Malicek, J" journalOrPublisher="Herzogia" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="431 - 444" refId="B14" refString="Malicek, J, Mayrhofer, H, 2017. Additions to the lichen diversity of Macedonia (FYROM) [Ergaenzungen zur Flechtendiversitaet von Makedonien (FYROM)]. Herzogia 30 (2): 431 - 444, DOI: https://doi.org/10.13158/heia.30.2.2017.431" title="Additions to the lichen diversity of Macedonia (FYROM) [Ergaenzungen zur Flechtendiversitaet von Makedonien (FYROM)]." url="https://doi.org/10.13158/heia.30.2.2017.431" volume="30" year="2017">
<normalizedToken id="182A0D8179F3F0576AD39E126C2A7F07" originalValue="Malíček">Malicek</normalizedToken>
and Mayrhofer 2017
</bibRefCitation>
) show that it differs in its black margin of areolae and absence of gyrophoric acid. This unknown species with lecanorine apothecia is possibly a member of 
<taxonomicName id="EBFFBDB3B0395C5A0F29E9BC666B3AD4" authorityName="C. M. Xie, Lu L. Zhang &amp; Li S. Wang" authorityYear="2022" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Lecaimmeria" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecaimmeria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="25A317B9F6B328B1D19141C875CBA2BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Lecaimmeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but descriptions are lacking and the specimens were not seen. Thus, this species is temporarily retained in 
<taxonomicName id="C5623829475C5D7135991CED27D96EFE" authorityName="Rambold &amp; Pietschm., Bibliotheca Lichenologica 34: 239" authorityYear="1989" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecideaceae" genus="Immersaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Immersaria" order="Lecideales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71DD97CEEFD4C906044B00953478D55E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Immersaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
